does not cause me pain.

212
00:09:13,235 --> 00:09:15,486
As rock and roll bad boy,
Paul Simon, once said,

213
00:09:15,488 --> 00:09:16,570
"I am a rock.

214
00:09:16,572 --> 00:09:18,822
I am an i-i-i-island."

215
00:09:19,991 --> 00:09:21,792
I'm calling him.

216
00:09:21,794 --> 00:09:23,660
Oh, goodie!
Put him on speakerphone!

217
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:28,582
(dance music playing)

218
00:09:30,452 --> 00:09:32,086
(phone vibrating)

219
00:09:32,088 --> 00:09:33,420
Excuse me, ladies,

220
00:09:33,422 --> 00:09:35,039
but my pants are buzzing.

221
00:09:35,041 --> 00:09:36,673
(vibrating continues)

222
00:09:37,425 --> 00:09:39,910
North Sea, how can I "kelp" you?

223
00:09:41,996 --> 00:09:42,963
Leonard?

224
00:09:42,965 --> 00:09:44,098
Penny?

225
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:45,215
Hey, it's Penny.

226
00:09:45,217 --> 00:09:46,416
Everybody say hi to Penny.

227
00:09:46,418 --> 00:09:48,102
ALL:
Hi, Penny!

228
00:09:48,104 --> 00:09:51,822
Wow, it sounds like
you're having a good time.

229
00:09:51,824 --> 00:09:54,708
Best time of my life!

230
00:09:56,311 --> 00:09:59,463
Isn't it 5:30
in the morning there?

231
00:09:59,465 --> 00:10:00,597
Is it?

232
00:10:00,599 --> 00:10:03,317
Hey, everybody,
it's 5:30 in the morning!

233
00:10:03,319 --> 00:10:05,352
(whooping)

234
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:06,870
Uh...

235
00:10:06,872 --> 00:10:08,756
okay, well,
we were just calling you

236
00:10:08,758 --> 00:10:10,273
because we were missing you.

237
00:10:10,275 --> 00:10:11,492
Iceberg!

238
00:10:11,494 --> 00:10:12,576
Uh-oh, hang on.

239
00:10:12,578 --> 00:10:14,211
Are you in danger?

240
00:10:14,213 --> 00:10:15,746
No, it's a drinking game.

241
00:10:15,748 --> 00:10:17,781
Whenever we see an iceberg,
we take a shot!

242
00:10:17,783 --> 00:10:19,833
ALL:
Berg! Berg!

243
00:10:19,835 --> 00:10:22,252
Berg! Berg! Berg! Berg--
(phone cuts off)

244
00:10:22,971 --> 00:10:24,254
Leonard, Leonard?

245
00:10:24,256 --> 00:10:26,473
(scoffs)

246
00:10:27,392 --> 00:10:30,094
I cannot believe we were
missing that jerk.

247
00:10:30,096 --> 00:10:32,913
<i>You</i> were.

248
00:10:41,603 --> 00:10:43,487
So what happened?
How'd it go?

249
00:10:43,489 --> 00:10:45,889
It's fine. I thanked them again
and let them know

250
00:10:45,891 --> 00:10:46,823
we're not available.

251
00:10:46,825 --> 00:10:48,975
So I can drink this
without having

252
00:10:48,977 --> 00:10:50,911
to give up the goodies?

253
00:10:50,913 --> 00:10:52,028
Yes, it's all cool.

254
00:10:52,030 --> 00:10:54,931
Although, if you wanted
to talk to one of them,

255
00:10:54,933 --> 00:10:56,249
no one would blame you.

256
00:10:56,251 --> 00:10:59,035
And why would no one
blame me?

257
00:10:59,871 --> 00:11:03,323
I don't know
what I'm saying.

258
00:11:03,325 --> 00:11:05,842
Well, it sounds
like you're saying

259
00:11:05,844 --> 00:11:07,594
that I could do better
than Sheldon.

